{"documentId":"e57a52d7-d1eb-4ed0-8b76-24b73b6f22c5","fileName":"sample_legal_case_file.pdf","filePath":"C:\\Users\\Aditya kumar thakur\\Desktop\\Legal-ai\\server\\storage\\uploads\\e57a52d7-d1eb-4ed0-8b76-24b73b6f22c5.pdf","textLength":1651,"createdAt":"2026-05-11T19:47:57.754Z","chunkConfig":{"chunkSize":1400,"chunkOverlap":220},"chunks":[{"id":"chunk-1","text":"IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF BENGALURU Civil Suit No. 142/2026 Case Information Case Title: Rajesh Kumar vs. ABC Constructions Pvt. Ltd. Date of Filing: 10 January 2026 Nature of Case: Breach of Contract and Compensation Claim Facts of the Case The plaintiff, Mr. Rajesh Kumar, entered into a construction agreement with ABC Constructions Pvt. Ltd. on 15 March 2025 for the construction of a residential property in Bengaluru. The agreement stated that the construction would be completed within eight months. The plaintiff alleges that the company failed to complete the project within the agreed timeline and used substandard construction materials, resulting in financial loss and structural defects. Claims by Plaintiff • Delay in project completion. • Violation of contractual obligations. • Financial losses due to rental expenses. • Mental stress and inconvenience caused by the delay. Defense by Defendant The defendant claims that the delay occurred due to supply chain disruptions and labor shortages caused by unexpected market conditions. The defendant also states that the plaintiff approved multiple design modifications during the construction period, which contributed to the delay. Relevant Legal Sections • Indian Contract Act, 1872 – Section 73. • Consumer Protection Act, 2019. • Specific Relief Act, 1963. Expected Legal Procedure 1. Filing of written statement by the defendant. 2.","start":0,"end":1399,"embedding":[0.06507061,0.037647963,-0.16006958,-0.027790327,0.021765722,-0.009901139,0.0267517,0.043502614,-0.011176462,-0.028318964,-0.02455567,0.019109681,0.019532409,-0.06973432,0.047775827,-0.024918912,0.04